"The truncated or zero-padded input, transformed along the axis indicated by "
"`axis`, or the last one if `axis` is not specified. The length of the "
"transformed axis is `n`, or, if `n` is not given, ``2*m - 2`` where ``m`` is "
"the length of the transformed axis of the input. To get an odd number of "
"output points, `n` must be specified, for instance as ``2*m - 1`` in the "
"typical case,"
msgstr ""

